Author: dspurkayastha <dshome45215@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Feb 20 20:51:09 2026 +0530

    Fix macro parameter character # error — sanitise markdown in front matter and appendices

    Root cause: Phase 1 AI content was pure Markdown (# headings, **bold**, ---
    separators) injected directly into main.tex via injectFrontMatter() without
    sanitisation. Pre-flight validation only checks chapter files (phases 2-8),
    not front matter or appendices injected into main.tex.

    Changes:
    - Apply sanitiseLatexOutput() in injectFrontMatter() to convert markdown → LaTeX
    - Apply sanitiseLatexOutput() in injectAppendices() for Phase 10 content
    - Add \subsection pattern matching for abstract split (handles sanitised ## headings)
    - Add FRONT MATTER and ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS heading cleanup for sanitised content
    - DB fix: converted Phase 1 markdown to LaTeX, removed truncated BibTeX entry

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Entire-Checkpoint: bd84f5776d75

