Perfect! Now I have all the relevant code. Let me create a comprehensive report with the code sections verbatim:

## Appendices/Annexure Injection Logic - Complete Analysis

### 1. **ANNEXURE_SECTION_MAP** (lines 404-408 in assemble.ts)

```typescript
const ANNEXURE_SECTION_MAP: Record<string, string> = {
  "Patient Information Sheet and Informed Consent Form": "Patient Information Sheet and Informed Consent Form",
  "Data Collection Proforma": "Data Collection Proforma",
  "Master Chart": "Master Chart",
};
```

This maps AI-generated `\section*{}` headings (keys) to template `\annexurechapter{}` names (values). The AI prompt instructs Phase 10 to use these exact section headings.

---

### 2. **injectAppendices() Function** (lines 417-476 in assemble.ts)

```typescript
function injectAppendices(
  tex: string,
  sections: Section[],
  warnings: string[]
): string {
  const phase10 = sections
    .filter((s) => s.phase_number === 10)
    .sort((a, b) => {
      const priority: Record<string, number> = { approved: 0, review: 1 };
      return (priority[a.status] ?? 2) - (priority[b.status] ?? 2);
    })[0];

  if (!phase10?.latex_content) return tex;

